Code ExamplesAdmonitionsLists and TablesIcons and Emojis <p>Here's how to include code blocks with syntax highlighting:</p> <pre><code>def hello_world():
    """A simple hello world function"""
    print("Hello, MkDocs!")
    return "success"

# Usage
result = hello_world()
</code></pre> <pre><code>// JavaScript example
const greeting = (name) =&gt; {
    return `Hello, ${name}! Welcome to MkDocs.`;
};

console.log(greeting("Developer"));
</code></pre> <p>Material for MkDocs supports various admonition types:</p> <p>Note</p> <p>This is a note admonition that highlights important information.</p> <p>Tip</p> <p>This tip provides helpful suggestions for users.</p> <p>Warning</p> <p>This warning alerts users about potential issues.</p> <p>Danger</p> <p>This danger alert indicates critical problems.</p> <p>Ordered Lists: 1. First step in your process 2. Second step with more details 3. Third step to complete the task</p> <p>Unordered Lists: - Feature one - Feature two     - Sub-feature A     - Sub-feature B - Feature three</p> <p>Tables:</p> Feature Description Status Search Built-in search functionality ✅ Available Themes Multiple theme support ✅ Available Plugins Extensible plugin system ✅ Available Mobile Responsive design ✅ Available <p>Material for MkDocs includes thousands of icons:</p> <ul> <li>:material-account: User accounts</li> <li>:material-bell: Notifications</li> <li>:material-cloud: Cloud services</li> <li>:material-code: Code examples</li> <li>:material-heart: Favorites</li> </ul> <p>Emoji Support: - 🎉 Celebration - 🚀 Getting started - 📚 Documentation - 🔍 Search functionality</p>
